---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Club">
  <Hero
    title="The Club"
    subtitle="A welcoming martial arts community built on tradition and respect"
    backgroundImage="/images/club-hero.jpg"
    ctaText="Join Our Community"
    ctaLink="/become-a-member"
  />
  
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="container-width max-w-4xl">
      <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
        <h2>A Family Atmosphere</h2>
        <p>
          Jan de Jong Martial Arts Fitness is more than just a place to learn martial arts - 
          it's a community. Our dojo has a family feel that is very warm and welcoming to both 
          new and existing students. We pride ourselves on creating an environment where everyone 
          feels supported and encouraged in their martial arts journey.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          All classes are conducted in a positive, friendly atmosphere of cooperation, not 
          competition. All students are encouraged to support and help each other, ensuring 
          an enjoyable and fruitful learning experience. This collaborative approach creates 
          lasting friendships and a strong sense of community among our members.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Inclusive Environment</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome students of all ages, backgrounds, and abilities. Our instructors are 
          skilled at adapting training to meet individual needs, whether you're a complete 
          beginner, returning to martial arts after time away, or an experienced practitioner 
          looking to expand your skills.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Student Support Network</h2>
        <p>
          One of the unique aspects of our club is how students support each other. Senior 
          students often mentor newcomers, creating a positive learning environment where 
          everyone benefits. This peer support system helps new students feel comfortable 
          and confident as they begin their martial arts journey.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Special Needs Welcome</h2>
        <p>
          We have extensive experience working with students who have special needs, including 
          those on the autism spectrum. Our instructors are patient, understanding, and skilled 
          at adapting teaching methods to ensure every student can participate and benefit from 
          martial arts training.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Community Events and Activities</h2>
        <p>
          Throughout the year, we organize various events and activities that bring our 
          community together outside of regular training. These include demonstrations, 
          social gatherings, and special training workshops that strengthen the bonds 
          between members.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Lifelong Friendships</h2>
        <p>
          Many of our students develop friendships that extend far beyond the dojo. The 
          shared experience of martial arts training, combined with our supportive community 
          atmosphere, creates connections that often last a lifetime.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Values We Share</h2>
        <p>
          Our club is built on core values of respect, discipline, perseverance, and mutual 
          support. These values are not just taught in our martial arts techniques but are 
          lived and demonstrated by our instructors and students every day.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-12 text-center bg-accent p-8 rounded">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-4">Join Our Martial Arts Family</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6">
          Experience the warmth and support of our community. Whether you're looking to 
          learn self-defence, improve fitness, or simply be part of something special, 
          you'll find a home at Jan de Jong Martial Arts Fitness.
        </p>
        <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center">
          <Button href="/free-trial">Try a Free Class</Button>
          <Button href="/contact" type="secondary">Visit Our Dojo</Button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>